Japan Seeks to Buy 32,381 Tons of Milling Wheat in Tender

-- B y   A y a   T a k a d a
-- 
2011-03-15T07:06:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/japan-seeks-to-buy-32-381-tons-of-milling-wheat-in-tender.html
  Japan  is seeking to buy 32,381
metric tons of milling wheat in a regular tender on March 17,
the Ministry of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries said.  Shipment is set from May 1 to May 31, Masafumi Otsuka at
the ministry’s grain-trade division said today by phone.  The ministry, which controls overseas purchases and
domestic sales of wheat to stabilize supply, is  Asia ’s largest
buyer as a single entity. It has bought 5.03 million tons this
fiscal year through regular tenders, surpassing the 4.26 million
tons of purchase in the year ended March 31, 2010.  Details of this week’s tender are listed below:  To contact the reporter on this story:
